  "body": "#### System information\r\nGeth version: master\r\n\r\n#### Problem\r\nCall whisperv5(6).PublicWhisperAPI.NewMessageFilter with one topic\r\nAt:\r\n``` go\r\n\tif len(req.Topics) > 0 {\r\n\t\ttopics = make([][]byte, 1)\r\n\t\tfor _, topic := range req.Topics {\r\n\t\t\ttopics = append(topics, topic[:])\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\nallocates slice with one element. Then using append it was adding next elemens(so, we got empty topic at topics slice).\r\n\r\nThen NotifyWatchers try to match envelop using function:\r\n``` go\r\nfunc matchSingleTopic(topic TopicType, bt []byte) bool {\r\n\tif len(bt) > 4 {\r\n\t\tbt = bt[:4]\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfor j, b := range bt {\r\n\t\tif topic[j] != b {\r\n\t\t\treturn false\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn true\r\n}\r\n```\r\nbut bt is empty. And range over bt is not working. So, **matchSingleTopic for empty topic is always true**\r\n\r\nLooks like, all whisper nodes(which message filters was created over PublicWhisperAPI try to decrypt every whisper message(with same key type).\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nCreated message filter with one topic\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nCreated message filter with two topics\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
